  "prompt": "What % of stories in Quora would be real?",
  "response": "The percentage of real stories on Quora can be difficult to determine precisely, as Quora is an open platform where anyone can contribute content. Users share personal experiences, knowledge, opinions, and sometimes fictional stories. While many users aim to provide accurate and truthful information, the nature of the platform means that the authenticity of content can vary.\n\nQuora relies on community moderation, where users upvote useful answers and report misleading or false information. Additionally, verified credentials and sources can add credibility to the posts. However, without rigorous fact-checking for every post, it is impossible to quantify exactly what percentage of the stories are real versus fictional or exaggerated.\n\nIt's important for readers to critically evaluate the information on Quora and cross-reference it with trusted sources when making decisions based on the content.",
